        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "Notes and context\n- The values above are overall formation constants (as indicated by the β-definitions returned: β1, β2, β3) and are reported as logK in SRD‑46.\n- All logK measurements listed for Cd–Cl in this pull were at 25 °C; ionic strength spanned 0, 0.5, 1, 2, 3, and 4 M.\n- Trend: conditional logK values for the higher chloro complexes (ML2, ML3) increase with ionic strength over 1–4 M, reflecting stronger complex formation at higher chloride activities. The 0 M entries appear as higher (thermodynamic) values compared with mid-range ionic strengths for β1 and β2.",
